817
01:09:41,649 --> 01:09:54,799
[SPEAKER_14]: So Anthony or Frank from the Collins Center, can you speak to the issue of ward bosses, maybe even to define that, what that might mean and how that might, how possible is that?

818
01:09:57,905 --> 01:10:02,471
[SPEAKER_04]: So I don't have any information right now to present to the committee on that.

819
01:10:02,551 --> 01:10:09,661
[SPEAKER_04]: I can look into studies about the political strength

820
01:10:12,162 --> 01:10:16,804
[SPEAKER_04]: inside a specific community with war council situations.

821
01:10:18,505 --> 01:10:26,628
[SPEAKER_04]: I can say that I've done some research relative to this committee, and I haven't seen any, but I can double-check specifically on that issue.

822
01:10:26,648 --> 01:10:35,492
[SPEAKER_04]: I mean, the stuff that I've seen is, to put it in sort of a pro and con context, is that, and this committee's already covered it, relative to,

823
01:10:37,953 --> 01:10:44,780
[SPEAKER_04]: ethnic or racial minority groups where representation is beneficial in terms of getting candidates elected.

824
01:10:45,761 --> 01:10:51,326
