878
01:15:18,331 --> 01:15:30,539
[SPEAKER_08]: But as we I was researching the feasibility of us conducting sort of a low budget focus group ran into some challenges that seemed a little insurmountable.

879
01:15:32,160 --> 01:15:34,582
[SPEAKER_08]: Both the Board of Health and the Collins Center.

880
01:15:35,608 --> 01:15:47,754
[SPEAKER_08]: we're concerned with the model of us leading the focus groups as potentially looking to residents like we sort of put our thumb on the scale of the outcomes.

881
01:15:48,614 --> 01:15:54,417
[SPEAKER_08]: And it might appear, even if we didn't appear to the results from the focus group could appear to be biased.

882
01:15:54,457 --> 01:16:03,942
[SPEAKER_08]: So both the Collins Center and the local board of health raise those as potential appearances that could harm the results.

883
01:16:05,342 --> 01:16:19,925
[SPEAKER_08]: and talking to Petty at the Board of Health, to hire someone to conduct the focus groups and potentially even analyze the data could run around $20,000.

884
01:16:20,905 --> 01:16:29,887
[SPEAKER_08]: Just to do the focus groups could be $3,000, but then to analyze all the data, which I thought maybe I could do, was a significant amount of money.

885
01:16:31,618 --> 01:16:58,583
[SPEAKER_08]: In talking about it with the work group, which was Maury, Milva, and Anthony, we decided we're going to not do focus groups, but instead do something similar, but isn't as technical or require as much resources, is to do listening sessions, which government entities do all the time.

