[SPEAKER_05]: They want to stand up and give their opinion.

1294
01:54:10,078 --> 01:54:10,978
[SPEAKER_05]: I have no problem with that.

1295
01:54:10,998 --> 01:54:14,080
[SPEAKER_05]: They're citizens, but I didn't want it to be a here they are.

1296
01:54:15,320 --> 01:54:17,282
[SPEAKER_05]: You know, I don't want to get too much.

1297
01:54:17,402 --> 01:54:21,004
[SPEAKER_14]: The question was, should we send them invitations?

1298
01:54:21,044 --> 01:54:30,191
[SPEAKER_11]: We tried to do the same thing in Oktoberfest to not make it a campaign political event, but we were stopped from saying you can't campaign or say anything.

1299
01:54:30,251 --> 01:54:39,658
[SPEAKER_11]: So what I'm saying is, you know, we have to be careful that if someone that's running for something gets upset, you know, how to take it from themselves.

1300
01:54:39,739 --> 01:54:40,899
[SPEAKER_11]: I mean, how we cut them off.

1301
01:54:40,979 --> 01:54:43,661
[SPEAKER_11]: I think it's got to be just watch it.

1302
01:54:43,702 --> 01:54:44,102
[SPEAKER_11]: That's all.

1303
01:54:44,402 --> 01:54:45,042
[SPEAKER_05]: No, I agree.

1304
01:54:45,062 --> 01:54:48,584
[SPEAKER_05]: I think everybody gets the same amount of time to speak whether who they are.

1305
01:54:48,604 --> 01:54:52,307
[SPEAKER_14]: Okay, so I want to be mindful because we have three minutes left.

1306
01:54:52,427 --> 01:54:53,788
[SPEAKER_14]: So, Francis.

1307
01:54:53,808 --> 01:55:01,712
[SPEAKER_01]: Yes, very quickly, if the firefighters club on Salem Street is only available by rental.

1308
01:55:02,092 --> 01:55:08,616
[SPEAKER_01]: Do you want me to look at the, the one in South Medford that I believe that's the one that has the community room.

1309
01:55:09,517 --> 01:55:10,697
[SPEAKER_01]: It does.

1310
01:55:11,058 --> 01:55:13,379
[SPEAKER_01]: Okay, I'll look at that as an alternative.

1311
01:55:14,015 --> 01:55:15,356
[SPEAKER_14]: Okay, thanks.

1312
01:55:15,736 --> 01:55:29,467
[SPEAKER_14]: Okay, the only other items on here were, we talked about survey outreach on election day, that maybe we could hold signs with the QR code at polling locations, but I don't know if we have the bandwidth for that.

1313
01:55:31,628 --> 01:55:37,753
[SPEAKER_14]: So that is, if anybody is interested in that, contact me and we'll see if we can make it happen.

1314
01:55:38,814 --> 01:55:41,235
[SPEAKER_14]: But our survey is open until December 1st.

1315
01:55:43,256 --> 01:55:47,498
[SPEAKER_14]: and we have about 400 responses right now.

1316
01:55:48,258 --> 01:55:53,661
[SPEAKER_14]: Okay, any other comments on these last items from the committee?

1317
01:55:56,102 --> 01:55:58,223
[SPEAKER_14]: Do we have any members of the public who wish to speak?

1318
01:56:00,404 --> 01:56:01,644
[SPEAKER_14]: I think everybody left.

1319
01:56:02,465 --> 01:56:03,345
[SPEAKER_14]: I don't know, maybe not.

1320
01:56:06,406 --> 01:56:07,587
[SPEAKER_14]: Yeah, I don't think there's anybody there.

1321
01:56:08,868 --> 01:56:09,208
[SPEAKER_14]: Okay.

1322
01:56:10,628 --> 01:56:11,009
[SPEAKER_14]: I mentioned-

1323
01:56:14,220 --> 01:56:19,564
[SPEAKER_14]: Yeah, our next meeting is November 2nd, but I will see most of you in a couple of weeks at City Hall.

1324
01:56:22,846 --> 01:56:25,108
[SPEAKER_14]: Thank you.

1325
01:56:26,169 --> 01:56:26,910
[SPEAKER_14]: Thanks, everybody.

1326
01:56:26,930 --> 01:56:27,710
[SPEAKER_14]: Bye.

1327
01:56:27,890 --> 01:56:28,251
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you.

1328
